    "Table 4 presents the vectors of average relevance values reported by our samples of self-reported GPT liberals and self-reported GPT conservatives, the aforementioned human samples of Graham et al. (2011), and their comparisons.",
    "To compare these vectors, we used the absolute-error (L 1) distance metric, the Euclidean (L 2) distance metric, and the cosine similarity metric.",
    "All three distance metrics found our sample of selfreported GPT conservatives to be most similar to conservative participants of Graham et al. (2011).",
    "This was always followed relatively closely by the moderate sample.",
    "The two furthest away were always the liberal sample (furthest away with respect to cosine similarity metric) and the libertarian sample (furthest away with respect to the L 1 and L 2 distance metrics)."
